content.text:
All export-related code lives in [templates/index.html](templates/index.html). Five sections:

### 1. CSS — button styling — [lines 181-196](templates/index.html#L181-L196)
```css
.btn-export {
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  background: var(--color-primary-light);
  color: var(--color-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-primary-mid);
  white-space: nowrap;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-2);
}
.btn-export:hover { background: var(--color-primary-mid); }
.btn-export:active { background: var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-text-inverse); }
.btn-export:disabled { opacity: 0.45; cursor: not-allowed; pointer-events: none; }
```

### 2. HTML — the button itself — [lines 654-665](templates/index.html#L654-L665)
```html
<!-- Export PDF -->
<button class="btn-export" id="btn-export"
        title="Export chat as PDF" aria-label="Export chat as PDF">
  <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
       stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" aria-hidden="true">
    <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"
          stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
    <polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
    <line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
  </svg>
  Export PDF
</button>
```

### 3. JS — DOM reference — [line 888](templates/index.html#L888)
```js
const btnExport     = document.getElementById('btn-export');
```

### 4. JS — click handler wiring — [line 936](templates/index.html#L936)
```js
btnExport.addEventListener('click', exportToPDF);
```

### 5. JS — the `exportToPDF()` function — [lines 1080-1159](templates/index.html#L1080-L1159)
This is the bulk of the logic. Broken down:

- **Lines 1083-1088** — guard: alert if there are no messages to export
- **Lines 1090-1092** — formatted date string for the document header
- **Lines 1094-1099** — `escapeHTML` helper so user content can't break the popup HTML
- **Lines 1101-1111** — `messagesHTML`: walks every `.message-row` (skipping typing indicators), reads the bubble text, builds a `<section class="msg user|coach">` per message
- **Line 1113** — builds the suggested filename (`coach-session-YYYY-MM-DD`) used as the document `<title>` (browsers offer it as the Save-as-PDF default name)
- **Lines 1115-1149** — `docHTML`: a complete self-contained HTML document string with embedded CSS (`@page`, fonts, colors, page-break rules) and a small bootstrap script that calls `window.print()` on load and closes the window after print
- **Lines 1151-1158** — opens a blank popup, writes the document into it, closes the stream. Alerts if the popup was blocked.

Nothing else in the project touches export — no backend route, no separate JS file, no external library (since we removed the jspdf script).

Per your earlier note, let me describe the changes first before touching the file. Here's what makes the current code look machine-written, and what I'd change:

### What looks "AI-generated" right now

1. **String concatenation with `+`** for the multi-line HTML/CSS. A human would use a template literal (backticks) so the HTML reads like HTML.
2. **Repetitive `.replace()` chain** in `escapeHTML` — six separate calls when one regex does it.
3. **Over-commented obvious lines** — comments like "Document header" and "Messages" that just restate what the next line does.
4. **Awkward conditional ternary in colors** — `isUser ? 61 : 100, isUser ? 139 : 95, isUser ? 122 : 90` (that one's already gone, but the style is similar elsewhere).
5. **Redundant `if (!bubble) return ''` then `text`-extract then `if (!text)`** — fine, but a human would more often use optional chaining: `row.querySelector('.bubble')?.textContent.trim()`.

### What it'd look like after

A condensed preview of the shape:
```js
function exportToPDF() {
  const rows = Array.from(chatArea.querySelectorAll('.message-row:not(.typing-row)'));
  if (rows.length === 0) {
    alert('Start a conversation first — there are no messages to export yet.');
    return;
  }

  const escapeHTML = s => s.replace(/[&<>"']/g, c => (
    { '&': '&amp;', '<': '&lt;', '>': '&gt;', '"': '&quot;', "'": '&#39;' }[c]
  ));

  const dateStr = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
    weekday: 'long', year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric',
  });

  const messages = rows.map(row => {
    const isUser = row.classList.contains('user');
    const text = row.querySelector('.bubble')?.textContent.trim();
    if (!text) return '';
    return `
      <section class="msg ${isUser ? 'user' : 'coach'}">
        <div class="who">${isUser ? 'YOU' : 'COACH'}</div>
        <div class="text">${escapeHTML(text)}</div>
      </section>`;
  }).join('');

  const fileTitle = `coach-session-${new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)}`;

  const html = `<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>${fileTitle}</title>
  <style>
    @page { size: letter; margin: 20mm; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      color: #2a2722;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 24px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    header     { border-bottom: 1px solid #dcdad4; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 18px; }
    h1         { font-size: 18px; color: #3d8b7a; margin: 0 0 4px 0; }
    .date      { font-size: 11px; color: #7a7670; }
    .msg       { padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eeece7; page-break-inside: avoid; }
    .msg:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .who       { font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .msg.user  .who { color: #3d8b7a; }
    .msg.coach .who { color: #645f5a; }
    .text      { font-size: 11.5px; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }
    footer     { margin-top: 24px; padding-top: 10px; border-top: 1px solid #dcdad4;
                 font-size: 9px; color: #b4b1ad; text-align: center; }
    @media print { body { padding: 0; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Neurodiversity Support Coach</h1>
    <div class="date">${dateStr}</div>
  </header>
  <main>${messages}</main>
  <footer>Neurodiversity Support Coach</footer>
  <script>
    window.addEventListener('load', () => {
      window.focus();
      window.print();
      window.addEventListener('afterprint', () => window.close());
    });
  <\/script>
</body>
</html>`;

  const win = window.open('', '_blank');
  if (!win) {
    alert('Please allow pop-ups to export the chat.');
    return;
  }
  win.document.open();
  win.document.write(html);
  win.document.close();
}
```

### Net effect

- **Same behavior** — output is identical
- **~80 lines → ~70 lines**, and the HTML/CSS reads as HTML/CSS instead of as JavaScript noise
- **Comments trimmed** to just the one-line summary above the function

Want me to apply this?

